investigation.title: Lunar gravity prevents skeletal muscle atrophy but not myofiber type shift in mice
investigation.description: Skeletal muscle is sensitive to gravitational alterations. We recently developed a multiple artificial-gravity research system (MARS), which can generate gravity ranging from microgravity to Earth gravity (1 g) in space.

project.funding: This work was supported by the Grant-in-Aid for the Japan Aerospace Exploration Agency (14YPTK-005512; S.T.), Grant-in-Aid for Scientific Research on Innovative Area from MEXT (18H04965; S.T.), and Research Fellowships for Young Scientists (DC2), JSPS (22J10954; T.H.).
